🟢  𝐃𝐞𝐭𝐞𝐜𝐭 𝐒𝐐𝐋 𝐈𝐧𝐣𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐕𝐮𝐥𝐧𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐛𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐞𝐬
In this section, we’ll detect Vulnerabilities from Kali Linux using tools such as SQL Map and Burp-Suite
📌 Scan Database for SQLi Vulnerabilities using SqlMap https://lnkd.in/dUH5V4tY

🟢 𝐄𝐱𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐒𝐐𝐋 𝐈𝐧𝐣𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬 𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐬
➡️ Retrieving hidden data
➡️ Blind SQL injection - Authentication Bypass[No error, No details, No clue and bypass login form]
➡️ Blind SQL injection - Boolean[No error, No details, No clue and response with YES/NO ]
➡️ Blind SQL injection - Time[No error, No details, No clue and Time to complete the query ]
➡️ SQL injection UNION attack[Starts with determining no. of columns]
➡️ Out-of-Band SQL Injection attack[It depends on business logic]
